    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I am thinking about one of the two\r\n1) launching the app and providing the private key in as a secure input and then keeping it in protected memory\r\n2) keeping the key on hard drive encrypted with salt and then using a password to decrypt it whenever signing the block and removing the key from memory straight after - the password would be introduced the same way as in 1) so I think that 1) is less convenient but more secure as there is only one attack vector - memory and not two - memory and hard drive (both are susceptible to intercepting key inputs on launch)\r\n\r\nthis is for the nodes that would not have hardware signer connected",
